    <h1>Extensions</h1>
    <p>Add extension interface can be used to add extensions to the Governance Registry. Simply upload the JAR
        file containing the extension using the interface shown in Figure 1.</p>
    <p>
        There are 3 types of extensions that you can add to the Registry using this interface.
    </p>

    <ul><li>
        Handlers
        </li>
    <li>
        Filters
        </li>
    <li>
        Aspects
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Details on these extensions can be found in Governance Registry Developer's Guide
    </p>

    <h2>List Extensions</h2>
    <p></p>
    <p>List extensions interface shown in Figure 1 can be used to list extensions added to the Governance Registry. It also provides a way
        to remove added extensions.</p>

    <p><img src="images/extensions_list.png" width="728"/></p>
    <p>Figure 1: Listing added extensions</p>

